The paper discusses a new test for learning causal networks from data, which is a topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Specifically, it focuses on constraint-based learning, which falls under the category of probabilistic graphical models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper involves statistical inference and hypothesis testing, which are relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
